        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-17 13:55:40.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nYang I might have misunderstood the ask.  \n\nI just recently updated the images for 2 pomba components https://gerrit.onap.org/r/#/c/87829/ and just trying to update this file to reflect them.  \n\nAnd also trying to find a way to indicate that some of POMBA components need to use older version of image (which is different from the version listed in the docker-manifest-staging.csv)",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "55a7ebba289baf2765d60585ff5c3e9a7478c9f0",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1077,
          "name": "Michael O'Brien",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "frank.obrien@amdocs.com",
          "username": "michaelobrien"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-17 14:15:56.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\njust a question - I thought we were deprecating the CSV's - although I understand the need for a staging version.  There is an issue with the shared images like data-router and search-data-service - the use by pomba will have to be older versions than what was in https://gerrit.onap.org/r/#/c/87586/",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "21656a16c074f4bdca57774dd1641212164d8361",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 35,
          "name": "Gary Wu",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "gary.wu@gmail.com",
          "username": "gwu"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-17 14:43:31.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThe staging CSV is still necessary so that integration can override certain images with the staging versions as necessary.  We don't expect a fix for the \"one image multiple versions\" issue with the CSV.  Ultimately the CSV needs to be converted to just a plain helm override file to deal with that issue.\n\nIf your team is currently working a bug fix and expect to release another version, then putting the staging version for that next release here will allow that staging version to be picked up by integration's staging deployments.  If you're not expecting to release any additional versions, then you should put the current release version in this CSV.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
